sec.p:
The MATLAB program r0exp is presented below. We avoided the explicit use of Equation (6). The built‐in function polyfit is used instead. 



function r0=r0exp(s,r);

% give 21 last percentage values of s (susceptible) ∖& r (recovered)

% embed successive exponential fits based on various past points


r0prev=‐1e16;r0=1e16;

k=2;r=r(:);s=s(:);


while abs(r0prev‐r0)>0.01 & k<21,

r0prev=r0;

r0=polyfit(r(end‐k:end),log(s(end‐k:end)),1);

r0=‐r0(1);

k=k+1;

end
